You can marry them.

363
00:23:09,510 --> 00:23:11,630
why would I do that?

364
00:23:12,310 --> 00:23:16,200
It's all we want.

365
00:23:16,480 --> 00:23:19,090
To have somebody say
that we're the one.

366
00:23:19,100 --> 00:23:21,710
If you do that,we'll
give you anything.

367
00:23:22,760 --> 00:23:24,630
Anything like what?

368
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:26,690
Secret stashes.

369
00:23:26,840 --> 00:23:29,600
We have 'em...

370
00:23:29,610 --> 00:23:31,280
because we think we're
going to be alone forever.

371
00:23:31,290 --> 00:23:34,070
So I take the money...

372
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:37,110
then I got a wife.
Forget it.

373
00:23:37,750 --> 00:23:40,040
- Divorce her.
- That's too messy.

374
00:23:42,790 --> 00:23:44,620
Get rid of her.

375
00:23:44,630 --> 00:23:46,400
that don't work,babe.

376
00:23:46,410 --> 00:23:48,690
I can't do jail.

377
00:23:50,410 --> 00:23:53,590
We can think of a way.

378
00:23:54,710 --> 00:23:56,770
For us to get
away with it.

379
00:23:57,080 --> 00:24:02,040
Us?

380
00:24:03,430 --> 00:24:05,110
People die every day
crossing the street.

381
00:24:05,120 --> 00:24:07,460
Martha...

382
00:24:10,220 --> 00:24:13,690
ramon.

383
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:16,540
Obviously,she wasn't serious
about taking anybody out.

384
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:19,650
Oh,obviously.

385
00:24:19,660 --> 00:24:22,430
People die crossing
the street?

386
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:24,810
That's how our five
women were taken out.

387
00:24:24,820 --> 00:24:27,200
Hit-and-runs were
martha's idea.

388
00:24:27,210 --> 00:24:29,820
She wasn't ramon's victim.

389
00:24:33,550 --> 00:24:35,820
She was his accomplice.

390
00:24:35,830 --> 00:24:37,980
Well this is a big,
fat waste of time.

391
00:24:37,990 --> 00:24:39,930
Solving a murderer's murder.

392
00:24:39,940 --> 00:24:41,700
Case gets closed...
all five of them.

393
00:24:41,710 --> 00:24:43,620
Doesn't matter how we
feel about the victim.

394
00:24:43,630 --> 00:24:45,150
She's not a victim.
She's a psycho.

395
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:47,080
She did it for love.

396
00:24:47,090 --> 00:24:50,600
Love with a two-bit hood.

397
00:24:51,880 --> 00:24:53,690
Ramon wasn't pickin' anyone
off until martha came in.

398
00:24:55,030 --> 00:24:58,110
That's my piece.

399
00:24:58,120 --> 00:25:02,720
I found a pattern in the
victims' credit card charges.

400
00:25:02,730 --> 00:25:05,560
Day she died,buella stiffler made
a purchase at a florist in new jersey.

401
00:25:05,570 --> 00:25:09,330
Anastasia farelli went
to the beauty parlor.

402
00:25:09,730 --> 00:25:12,930
And petunia marshall
got a five-point wax.

403
00:25:12,940 --> 00:25:14,860
It's martha's wedding plan in
action. Flowers,the primping.

404
00:25:14,870 --> 00:25:18,040
Purchases were made
on the day they died.

405
00:25:18,050 --> 00:25:21,030
He was marrying them,and then kills 'em
before they have to pay for a honeymoon.

406
00:25:21,040 --> 00:25:23,840
They did the ceremony,offed the
girls and never filed the paperwork.

407
00:25:23,850 --> 00:25:26,550
Which would explain why there's no
record of ramon delgado being married.

408
00:25:26,560 --> 00:25:30,120
I called the florist in atlantic
city,where buella used her card.

409
00:25:30,130 --> 00:25:32,020
They said they doo a lot of orders
for the quickie chapel next door.

410
00:25:32,030 --> 00:25:35,270
Midnight love chapel,it's called.

411
00:25:50,160 --> 00:25:53,080
I'll send nick and
scotty down there.

412
00:25:55,650 --> 00:25:58,860
I can do it,but it's
not legal in this state.

413
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:02,060
Yeah,I remember rico suave
and the two big girls.

414
00:26:03,600 --> 00:26:06,730
buella and serena.

415
00:26:06,740 --> 00:26:08,000
This "serena" by any chance?

416
00:26:08,010 --> 00:26:10,840
Yep,that's her.

417
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:12,710
Serena montagne.
The groom's sister.

418
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:16,030
Sister?

419
00:26:16,140 --> 00:26:18,730
Tell us about serena
and her brother ramon.

420
00:26:18,740 --> 00:26:22,630
I've seen some wacky
couples in here,

421
00:26:31,470 --> 00:26:33,340
but that brother and
sister duo make my top five.

422
00:26:33,350 --> 00:26:35,220
S you two don't look alike.

423
00:26:36,130 --> 00:26:38,500
I'm adopted.!!

424
00:26:41,650 --> 00:26:42,970
I'm adopted.

425
00:26:42,980 --> 00:26:45,340
Hey,baby.

426
00:26:45,350 --> 00:26:47,060
Maybe you should check the
girls' room. Maybe she split.

427
00:26:47,070 --> 00:26:49,900
No,she's coming,ramon.

428
00:26:50,650 --> 00:26:53,050
She's been in there 40 minutes.
What'd you say to her?

429
00:26:53,060 --> 00:26:57,420
The first time you saw her tape,

430
00:26:57,880 --> 00:27:00,490
it was like you got tunnel vision
and all you could see was her,

431
00:27:00,500 --> 00:27:04,640
and then you called me from
a payphone and you said,

432
00:27:08,950 --> 00:27:11,350
sis,I can't believe it.
I think I found the one.

433
00:27:15,160 --> 00:27:17,790
That's nice.

434
00:27:20,840 --> 00:27:23,290
You look hot in a hat.

435
00:27:23,460 --> 00:27:26,660
I wish it were me.

436
00:27:28,100 --> 00:27:30,690
Walkin' down the aisle to you.

437
00:27:43,110 --> 00:27:45,280
Wouldn't mom be proud?

438
00:27:55,050 --> 00:27:58,540
well,hi.

439
00:27:58,550 --> 00:27:59,590
serena montagne-- name martha used--
it's from one of her romance novels.

440
00:27:59,600 --> 00:28:02,900
No kiddin'.

441
00:28:02,910 --> 00:28:05,520
Yeah,a busty milkmaid
finds out she's a princess.

442
00:28:10,890 --> 00:28:12,250
Isn't that always the way?
Thanks a lot.

443
00:28:12,260 --> 00:28:15,050
Hey,these bubbles?

444
00:28:16,540 --> 00:28:18,190
yep. Less mess than birdseed.

445
00:28:18,200 --> 00:28:20,010
you givin' these away in '89?

446
00:28:20,020 --> 00:28:21,980
Since we opened.

447
00:28:23,110 --> 00:28:25,230
Help yourself.

448
00:28:25,240 --> 00:28:27,620
Bells and bubbles.

449
00:28:28,050 --> 00:28:31,970
For free. It's your lucky day.

450
00:28:35,350 --> 00:28:37,170
Crackhead who saw buella's hit-and-run
talked about bells and bubbles.

451
00:28:37,180 --> 00:28:39,320
We're looking for.. Cherry lesure.

452
00:28:40,610 --> 00:28:44,930
I'm outta breath from
runnin' over here.

453
00:28:45,300 --> 00:28:47,110
My girlfriend said there was a delicious
scoop o' chocolate in a suit lookin' for me.

454
00:28:50,290 --> 00:28:51,790
Hello.

455
00:28:51,800 --> 00:28:54,020
cherry lesure?

456
00:28:54,030 --> 00:28:56,800
Detectives jeffries and rush.

457
00:28:56,810 --> 00:28:58,600
Back in '89,you saw a
hit-and-run down here.

458
00:28:58,610 --> 00:29:00,480
Big girl,buella stiffler.

459
00:29:00,490 --> 00:29:03,150
Dark days for me.

460
00:29:03,160 --> 00:29:05,260
You recall the incident or not?

461
00:29:05,750 --> 00:29:08,120
He always this feisty?

462
00:29:08,130 --> 00:29:10,670
I told them boys
in blue what I saw.

463
00:29:10,680 --> 00:29:14,470
They chose not to listen. Feisty.

464
00:29:14,480 --> 00:29:17,410
You described seeing
bells and bubbles.

465
00:29:17,420 --> 00:29:18,610
That's right. 'Cause they
were doin' a housewarming party.

466
00:29:18,620 --> 00:29:23,470
What do you mean?

467
00:29:27,700 --> 00:29:29,030
It's crazy,but they came down here
and acted like they found paradise.

468
00:29:32,650 --> 00:29:34,930
Watch your step.

469
00:29:34,940 --> 00:29:36,460
keep them closed. No looking.

470
00:29:36,470 --> 00:29:38,210
You guys are hysterical.

471
00:29:38,220 --> 00:29:41,110
Where are we?

472
00:29:41,120 --> 00:29:43,080
oh,you'll see in
a sec. No looking.

473
00:29:44,780 --> 00:29:47,130
- Okay.
